wiki.summary: Mo Bamba" is a single by American rapper Sheck Wes. It was released on June 16, 2017, by Cactus Jack Records, GOOD Music and Interscope Records. It serves as a single from his debut studio album, Mudboy. The song was produced by 16yrold and record production duo Take a Daytrip. The song was a sleeper hit, going viral in mid-2018 and peaking at #6 on the Hot 100. The song was named after Sheck Wes' friend, basketball player Mohamed Bamba. Read more on Last.fm.
